# ✅ 1. Basic Functional Component

```javascript
import React, { useState } from "react";

function CounterInput() {
  const [value, setValue] = useState(0);

  const MIN = 0;
  const MAX = 10;

  // Handle manual input
  const handleChange = (e) => {
    const val = e.target.value;

    // Allow empty input
    if (val === "") {
      setValue("");
      return;
    }

    // Only numbers
    if (!/^\d+$/.test(val)) return;

    const number = Number(val);

    if (number >= MIN && number <= MAX) {
      setValue(number);
    }
  };

  // Increment
  const increment = () => {
    setValue((prev) => Math.min(prev + 1, MAX));
  };

  // Decrement
  const decrement = () => {
    setValue((prev) => Math.max(prev - 1, MIN));
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>
      <h3>Counter with Validation</h3>

      <button onClick={decrement} disabled={value <= MIN}>
        -
      </button>

      <input
        type="text"
        value={value}
        onChange={handleChange}
        style={{ margin: "0 10px", width: "50px", textAlign: "center" }}
      />

      <button onClick={increment} disabled={value >= MAX}>
        +
      </button>

      <p>Min: {MIN}, Max: {MAX}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

export default CounterInput;
```

***

# ✅ 2. Validation Logic Explained

***

## 🔹 Numeric validation

```javascript
/^\d+$/.test(val)
```

✔ Only allows digits  
❌ Rejects letters/symbols

***

## 🔹 Min / Max validation

```javascript
Math.min(prev + 1, MAX)
Math.max(prev - 1, MIN)
```

✔ Ensures value stays within limits

***

## 🔹 Empty input handling

```javascript
if (val === "") setValue("");
```

✔ Avoids crashing when user clears input

